ry to Gmail","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"aec5236a-b55b-4e1f-bebf-43d085c368ad","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"062c4ecc-9a76-4ea9-94a1-3769f91847b7","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"5de089bc-e76a-4207-a702-ea3bb13e7f41","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[4833,1420],"id":"10814bfb-2455-4556-991a-993fa2a74d3c","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"sendTo":"={{ $json.email || 'ops@company.com' }}","subject":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage ","message":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.gmail","typeVersion":2.1,"position":[5157,1420],"id":"3927b045-1ae9-4d8f-8f95-489185bbe40f","name":"Escalate Failure to Gmail","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Receive Inbound Webhook\n\nEntry point: listens for POST calls on `/wf01076-request`. Use the TEST url while building, switch callers to the PRODUCTION url after publishing.\n\nNext: Collect Raw Text","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"2072379c-9f5e-53e1-be72-64e1c1bccc52","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Collect Raw Text\n\nShapes the item: writes `content`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Extract Structured Fields","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"beae0ea0-466c-165d-3609-5d4e4806312b","name":"Note: Collect Raw Text"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Extract Structured Fields\n\nPulls structured fields (requestId, query, context) out of free text using a strict extraction prompt.\n\nPorts: ①→ All Required Fields Found? · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"248a64aa-2db2-ad9d-662e-fa522a96fd85","name":"Note: Extract Structured Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenAI Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `gpt-4o-mini`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Extract Structured Fields** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenAI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[561,1090],"id":"5a048926-2448-8719-74b3-11b865893afa","name":"Note: OpenAI Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### All Required Fields Found?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.output?.requestId }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Upsert into MySQL · ②→ Queue for Manual Review","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,520],"id":"27df1d66-6564-521f-ca36-c9c7dccbddec","name":"Note: All Required Fields Found?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Upsert into MySQL\n\nmySql — `insert` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Review Paths · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 MySQL connection","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,280],"id":"11fb0104-c71c-976f-1536-1380446f5516","name":"Note: Upsert into MySQL"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Queue for Manual Review\n\ngmail — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Review Paths · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,880],"id":"cb9b47d2-27a2-b700-d67a-c8f2bc11e8c0","name":"Note: Queue for Manual Review"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Review Paths\n\nRejoins 2 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty query","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2181,520],"id":"5e0c39fe-f58d-fe3e-0537-f2175e056020","name":"Note: Merge Review Paths"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty query\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3153,520],"id":"388c8f71-254c-3978-396b-d48ab705ffa8","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty query"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Tag Pipeline Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3477,520],"id":"8421b976-0e32-db76-c278-1b06b24409b0","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3801,520],"id":"72141a22-0aee-e78b-a440-c1b8942af3ac","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 50 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4125,520],"id":"0482f026-b528-fd00-9f86-d0241fbd5931","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,520],"id":"14e4bdcf-aacb-fd9c-9725-c2a42a003dd1","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (MySQL)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"c029ffe0-982a-0349-a601-0ec813b7aab0","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (MySQL)\n\nmySql — `insert` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Gmail · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 MySQL connection","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"e21d7f7e-ccfa-4ae4-4130-d832f4375901","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (MySQL)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Gmail\n\ngmail — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,520],"id":"7e14d7ac-6794-329a-94af-fe8318b2e773","name":"Note: Send Summary to Gmail"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Gmail","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,1540],"id":"285d9224-fc2e-c9cd-6f0e-3c4b2fdf3f93","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Gmail\n\ngmail — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,1540],"id":"cabcc1d8-8f73-b902-1863-63d056c610a8","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Gmail"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Summarize meeting notes with MySQL and Gmail in real time\n\n**Pattern:** AI Summarize & Route · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nSummarize meeting notes with MySQL and Gmail in real time. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual task automation is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Collect Raw Text → Extract Structured Fields → All Required Fields Found? → Upsert into MySQL → Merge Review Paths → Guard Non-Empty query → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai summarize & route without manual effort\n- Anyone automating task automation in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2; MySQL connection; OpenAI API key.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"a2d4d17b-dfbc-3e88-bd12-7db3f27a0684","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-260],"id":"14dfe61a-0150-6ab4-14a9-5892da7bf90b","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-260],"id":"e6322340-6d42-02a0-0166-931e877c957a","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-260],"id":"37518ce3-3f90-4574-f25d-4ac5dc6bb8fe","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your task automation process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-260],"id":"a97dc362-dedd-32f6-7847-5bbf1fd84b02","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect Raw Text","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Collect Raw Text":{"main":[[{"node":"Extract Structured Fields","type":"main","index":0}]]},"OpenAI Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Extract Structured Fields","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Extract Structured Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"All Required Fields Found?","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"All Required Fields Found?":{"main":[[{"node":"Upsert into MySQL","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Queue for Manual Review","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Upsert into MySQL":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Review Paths","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Queue for Manual Review":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Review Paths","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Merge Review Paths":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty query","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty query":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (MySQL)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (MySQL)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Gmail","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Gmail","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Gmail":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"76a7f94f-5306-44bf-ae80-5a8262809bc9","id":"FDX01076"}